#1 Metastatic colon cancer to the pelvis with a history of breast cancer, Hodgkin's lymphoma, and tongue cancer
Mrs. Cason is a very pleasant 47-year-old female with a complicated prior past medical history seeking treatment recommendations for her metastatic colon cancer.
We discussed the characteristics of the cancer, including type of malignancy, size, grade, lymph node status.  We discussed the stage of the cancer and that the oncologist today would attempt to quantify the potential risk of cancer recurrence.  I will staff this with Dr. Sidney Moritz through the Oncology GI Clinic, who will outline his recommendations in his subsequent note.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: Yes, not on file at Mullen Dental Hospital.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

[end section id="20112"]

